The paper proposes a modification to the batch normalization technique commonly used in deep learning, which is a topic within the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The experiments are conducted on image datasets, which further supports the relevance to these sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of batch normalization for training on mobile or embedded devices, which suggests a potential connection to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed method involves computing statistics along different dimensions, which could be related to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments with image classification, which could also be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
